div.p:
To one, a Woman may be Constant;
but if she divides her Affections between
two, she can be Constant to neither.

Chuse for your Wife a Prudent Woman;
for Prudence preserves Vertue,
Vertue Love, and Love Constancy.

Shun a Woman that's your Enemy;
for every time she sees you it puts her
upon fresh Mischiefs.
